      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition and material property inputs verified against COU specification.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed all boundary condition specifications, material property assignments, and solver settings prior to production runs. No discrepancies found. Use error factor satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison of k-omega SST, k-epsilon realizable, and LES on representative operating point; hemolysis model (power-law) sensitivity to model constants documented.",
      "rationale": "Three turbulence models compared at 5 L/min, 3000 RPM. k-omega SST yielded lowest NIH prediction error (9%) versus experimental. Power-law hemolysis model constants (C=1.8e-6, alpha=0.765, beta=2.416) sensitivity analysis performed via Monte Carlo; 95th percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty distributions assigned to all influential input parameters; Monte Carlo propagation with N≥1000 samples performed; 95th-percentile NIH reported.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with N=2000 Latin hypercube samples. Uncertain inputs include blood viscosity (±8%), inlet velocity profile (±5%), rotational speed (±1%), and hemolysis model constants (literature-derived distributions). 95th-percentile NIH is 0.0087 g/100 L, below the 0.01 g/100 L threshold."
    },
